   "source": [
    "# Experiment 1: Baseline Model Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook explores the behavior of a simple rule-based classifier used to analyze emotionally ambiguous text.\n",
    "\n",
    "The goal is to identify failure modes and evaluate how the model performs in human-centered scenarios, particularly in mental health contexts."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from src.failure_analysis import classify_response"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "test_data = [\n",
    "    (\"I feel okay today.\", \"Neutral\"),\n",
    "    (\"I don’t know what to do anymore.\", \"Negative\"),\n",
    "    (\"Everything is fine!\", \"Negative\"),\n",
    "    (\"I feel lost and overwhelmed.\", \"Negative\"),\n",
    "    (\"Life is great.\", \"Positive\")\n",
    "]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "results = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for text, label in test_data:\n",
    "    prediction = classify_response(text)\n",
    "    results.append((text, prediction, label))\n",
    "\n",
    "results"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "correct = sum(1 for _, pred, true in results if pred == true)\n",
    "total = len(results)\n",
    "\n",
    "accuracy = correct / total\n",
    "accuracy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "for text, pred, true in results:\n",
    "    print(f\"Input: {text}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Prediction: {pred} | Actual: {true}\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Observations\n",
    "\n",
    "- The model struggles with emotionally ambiguous language such as \"okay\" or \"fine\"\n",
    "- Implicit distress is often misclassified as neutral or positive\n",
    "- The classifier relies heavily on keyword matching, limiting its ability to understand context\n",
    "\n",
    "## Key Failure Mode\n",
    "\n",
    "The most critical issue is the model’s inability to detect hidden or indirect distress, which is common in real-world mental health scenarios.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Insight\n",
    "\n",
    "This demonstrates that surface-level sentiment detection is insufficient for human-centered AI applications. More context-aware approaches are required."
